{"id":"math120-defint210-app003","cid":"MATH 120","topic":"Applications of Integration","subtopic":"Area under a curve","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"Find the area of the region bounded by f(x) = x^{n}, x = {lo}, x = {hi}, and the x-axis.","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":1},"n":{"type":"int","min":2,"max":3},"lo":{"type":"int","min":0,"max":1},"hi":{"type":"int","min":2,"max":4}},"answer_expr":"defint210","steps":["Area = integral from {lo} to {hi} of x^{n} dx.","= [x^{n+1}/({n+1})] from {lo} to {hi} = ({hi_pow} - {lo_pow}) / ({n+1}) = {answer_defint210} sq units."],"tags":["survey-calculus","area","definite-integral","bounded-region"]}
